      "name": "Webhook",
      "webhookId": "sabnzbd",
      "notes": "SABnzbd \u2014 download client status and control. Use for checking downloads, speed, and managing the download queue.\n\nActions:\n  queue \u2014 current downloads with progress, speed, and ETA. Use for \"what's downloading\", \"download progress\", \"download queue\".\n  history \u2014 recently completed and failed downloads. Use for \"what finished downloading\", \"recent downloads\", \"any failed downloads\".\n  status \u2014 overall download status including speed, disk space, and queue state. Use for \"download speed\", \"disk space\", \"is downloading paused\".\n  pause \u2014 pause the download queue. Use for \"pause downloads\", \"stop downloading\".\n  resume \u2014 resume the download queue. Use for \"resume downloads\", \"start downloading again\".\n  speed_limit \u2014 set download speed limit. Use for \"limit download speed\", \"set speed to 5MB\", \"remove speed limit\".\n\nRules:\n- speed_limit value can be a percentage (e.g. \"50\" for 50%), absolute (e.g. \"5M\" for 5 MB/s, \"500K\" for 500 KB/s), or \"0\" to remove the limit.\n\n---schema\n{\n  \"action\": {\n    \"type\": \"string\",\n    \"description\": \"One of: queue, history, status, pause, resume, speed_limit\",\n    \"required\": true\n  },\n  \"limit\": {\n    \"type\": \"integer\",\n    \"description\": \"Max items to return. Default 10. For: queue, history\"\n  },\n  \"speed\": {\n    \"type\": \"string\",\n    \"description\": \"Speed limit value. Examples: '50' (50%), '5M' (5 MB/s), '500K' (500 KB/s), '0' (unlimited). For: speed_limit\"\n  }\n}",
      "id": "sabnzbd-wbhk-0001-0000-000000000001"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "let data;\nconst input = $input.item.json;\n\nif (typeof input.body === 'string') {\n  data = JSON.parse(input.body);\n} else if (typeof input.body === 'object') {\n  data = input.body;\n} else {\n  data = input;\n}\n\nconst action = (data.action || '').toLowerCase().trim();\n\nif (!action) {\n  return [{ json: { error: true, message: 'Action is required. Use one of: queue, history, status, pause, resume, speed_limit.' } }];\n}\n\nconst validActions = ['queue', 'history', 'status', 'pause', 'resume', 'speed_limit'];\nif (!validActions.includes(action)) {\n  return [{ json: { error: true, message: `Unknown action: ${action}. Use one of: queue, history, status, pause, resume, speed_limit.` } }];\n}\n\nconst limit = parseInt(data.limit) || 10;\nconst speed = data.speed || '0';\n\nreturn [{ json: { action, limit, speed } }];"
      },
